##One cover-up led to 55 quarantines, and 55 close contacts were identified

The papernews

The function introduction, has the connotation the current politics new media

The following article is from the Morning News, written by Sun Limei

A network of all the news morning news that day important news detailed report, morning news activities

Sun Limei / Zhou to Shanghai client

On February 13, the Jinshan District branch of the Shanghai Public Security Bureau took criminal compulsory measures against Li Mou, a 60-year-old man who had been cured and discharged from a hospital in Jinshan District, Shanghai, for allegedly obstructing the prevention and treatment of infectious diseases. This is the outbreak since the first case in Shanghai on suspicion of obstructing the prevention and treatment of infectious diseases to take criminal compulsory measures.

The Shanghai Public Security Bureau said in the announcement that Li had concealed the fact of returning to Shanghai from key areas during his medical treatment and had repeatedly visited public places, leading to the isolation of 55 close contacts for observation, with serious consequences.

As well as expressing outrage at those who have deliberately withheld information, the question is: How on Earth have these 55 close contacts been identified?

Jinshan district CDC Infectious Disease Prevention and Control Section Chief Song Canlei answered this question.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Song Canlei interview with the Morning News, photography, Yang Mei

Including Song Canlei, Shanghai a large number of flow (epidemiological investigation) personnel are fighting in the forefront of the epidemic prevention and control positions. From receiving the report of suspected cases from the hospital, the flow of staff to quickly find out their source of infection, movement trajectory, contact with the crowd, and close contacts to their streets, communities, the first time to take isolation measures.

It is their Split Second and meticulous work that allows Shanghai residents to see "confirmed cases in areas and places" in daily disease reports, and the expression "all identified close contacts have been quarantined for medical observation, and all communities where cases have been confirmed have been notified, " in order to create an adequate sense of security in the neighborhood and city in which they live.

Because of this, some netizens gave the migrant workers a cool nickname: drug hunter.

Out in the rain

There are two flow regulation standards: "The shortest time" and "no omission"

From January 20, the first confirmed case in Shanghai, Song Canlei's Jinshan district CDC, began a round-the-clock epidemic prevention and control model.

CDC Emergency Room on duty, 24-hour shift staff on duty.

Every time a suspected case is reported, the flow dispatchers have to be dispatched quickly to check the patient's condition with the hospital's attending doctor, and follow the work flow, through telephone or face-to-face with patients in isolation ward to understand their basic personal situation, the onset of medical treatment, before and after the onset of movement track and contact of suspected cases, determine close contact group, and finally form an investigation report.

This is a war without guns. In order to find the source of infection, cut off the transmission route, the flow of dispatchers every time they receive a report like the enemy, ready.

"It takes about five to six hours from the time a case is reported to the lab for the first test result, " he said. "We really don't have a lot of time. Our biggest fear is that we will miss any close contacts. "

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Flow departure

Song Canlei said, no matter how complicated the case report, "the shortest time" and "no missing" is the flow of work must not discount the two standards. Because only in the shortest time to track and remind each close contact, in order to maximize the protection of one or even a large group of people.

Each suspected case is tested twice, both times negative, the suspected case can be ruled out, previously investigated close contacts will be notified immediately. This also is equal to say, the song can Lei all work that aims at this suspected case, be in fact"white do".

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Laboratory of Jinshan District Center for Disease Control

And this kind of "doing nothing" basically happens every day.

The first suspected case reported in Jinshan District was on January 25, the first night of the Lunar New Year. A fever clinic in a hospital in the district received two couples from key areas to visit their families in Shanghai, both have fever with pneumonia symptoms. Song and his colleagues set off for the hospital within 15 minutes, because the couple's activities and personal contact before and after the onset of illness were clear and the investigation was relatively smooth, but when song finished sorting out the investigation report, it's the early morning of the second day of the New Year.

A few hours later, the first lab test came back negative. The second test, still negative, was ruled out.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
In the middle of a diversion

From January 25 to the evening of February 19, the Jinshan District Center for Disease Control and Prevention received a total of 58 hospital reports of suspected cases, the final 3 cases were confirmed.

Song told the morning news reporter, he and his colleagues every action, are ready to fight a hard battle.

"The nature of our work is very special. When we get a call, we go all out, we get ready, but at the same time, from the inside, we'd rather be chasing our tails, chasing our tails. Of course, it is also a kind of training for us, and our working ability and value are all demonstrated in the process."

To investigate the most complex cases in an isolation ward

Li, who has now been subjected to criminal coercion, is the second of three confirmed cases in Jinshan District and the most complex case handled by song and his colleagues.

February 2 at 11:50 am, the CDC Emergency Phone: A hospital reported a suspected case of Li, fever with cough, fatigue and pneumonia, there are many days of key areas of travel history, and has been in the hospital in a number of departments.

Song, a veteran of the transfer, was keenly aware that this might not be an ordinary case and decided to form an experienced temporary team. At 12:10, the CDC dispatched a total of six mobile staff, including the city's CDC in Jinshan District, two experts. Previous investigations of suspected cases have been done in pairs.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Material Verification

In the hospital to understand the more than days of Li's medical records, Song Canlei found the seriousness of the situation.

Li arrived in Shanghai from Nanchang, Jiangxi Province, on January 24 and was staying at a hotel in Songjiang District. He developed cold symptoms that night, but thought "maybe he was under the covers" .

The next day, Li took a taxi from Songjiang District to his home in Jinshan District, where he took a taxi and went to a convenience store.

Since January 26, Li has been to the hospital for respiratory medicine, emergency medicine, Chinese medicine, infection, and other departments, almost every day in the hospital, but when the doctor asked about the history of epidemiology, he only told the doctor that he had come from Nanchang, Jiangxi Province.

Li's unusual increase in visits has also raised suspicions among doctors. Under cross-examination, Li finally revealed that he had been in Nanchang before, Wuhan, Huanggang and other three or four days of travel history, was sent to the fever clinic on February 2.

From the onset of illness on January 24 to entering the fever clinic on February 2, Li worked with medical staff, other patients, taxi drivers, hotel attendants and supermarket staff for several consecutive days, at the time, it was unclear whether there were any more likely close contacts. The length of its time span, the number of contacts, the complexity of the situation, eye-popping.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Information Verification

Before Li Mou, Song Canlei and colleagues understand the situation by telephone with suspected cases, according to the work specifications, mainly through hospital assistance.

"But Li's situation is very special. First, he is 60 years old, has a poor memory and lives alone, with no family to help him recall;

Second, his track is complex, and we need to master the track of each point in time, which can not leave space;

And then we learned that when the community asked him about it, he was probably not in the best physical condition to cooperate.

In this case, if the telephone survey, the effect may be very very poor. So we finally decided that one of my colleagues and I would go into the isolation room in a level 2 suit and do a face-to-face investigation."

Dozens of hours of hospital surveillance, covering every angle

What was it like being a non-clinician, entering an isolation ward face-to-face with a highly suspected case?

"There's definitely psychological pressure, especially when you go in there, it's a little bit intense, but with face-to-face communication, it's a slow, slow release.

Because the more you look into it, the more interesting you find the case, and in a way it feels like an accomplishment. Is that weird for me to say? (laughter) maybe it's just a professional instinct. In the end, the mood is completely relaxed."

Since entering the isolation ward at 1:30 pm on February 2, Song and his colleagues have been in the isolation ward for nearly two hours. Through a recording pen, they have recorded Li's detailed activity track and corresponding time since the day he became ill.

Song said the investigation was conducted without regard for feelings, but when he took off his protective clothing at the end of the investigation, he and his colleagues found that the clothes were soaked through.

From the hospital at 3:30 p.m. on February 2nd. But the battle is only just beginning.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Song Canlei, photography, Yang Mei

Song Canlei received a district epidemic prevention and Control Command clear instructions: Close contact list, must be out before the test results! The weight of the list, and the consequences it may have, speak for itself.

Song and his colleagues combed through Li's movements over the past 10 days, so that each point in time had a corresponding location. Inside the hospital, the hospital cooperated with the CDC to access the surveillance video, and other public places, the Public Security Bureau to assist in the investigation.

According to the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention, close contacts in the hospital would make up the majority of patients -- a prediction that was confirmed by subsequent data. Of the 55 close contacts eventually identified, 47 occurred inside the compound.

The Centers for Disease Control and prevention pulled daily surveillance footage of Li's hospital visits, totaling dozens of hours. As long as the figure of Li appears in the video, Song Canlei and his colleagues will click the mouse to track the way, about 2 meters in its vicinity, and then Zoom in and scrutinize: Li and the other party did not wear a mask, respectively, whether the medical staff took adequate precautions..

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Hospital surveillance, screening,

It took more than four hours just to look at the security footage.

"We keep track of every relevant point in time, with particular attention to specific actions. For example, when Li took off his mask, he took off his mask in the process of a few people passing by, these people also took off their mask at what time, when put on."

After watching the video, Song's colleagues went to each of the relevant departments and reassembled the tape to determine the estimated location, distance, and other data related to close contacts, all in line with the actual situation.

According to the infusion room location map, and monitor a pair of faces

The hospital's biggest problem is in the emergency room. Because Li's stay in other departments was relatively short, and his contact with people was relatively limited, but he had two consecutive infusions in two days, and his stay in the infusion room was more than two hours, the hospital's 79-seat IV room is already a crowded place.

Song Canlei said that it was more fortunate that they asked the hospital in detail to confirm that the window of the infusion room was open to maintain ventilation at that time, "according to the requirements of the state and Shanghai, if it is a confined space, then all patients present at that time need to be quarantined, and then the number will be even higher. "

Song and his colleagues took photos and measured the location map of the infusion room, and finally Li's location as the center, according to the left and right four positions (about 2 meters) , before and after 2 rows (about 1.5 meters) , the initial delineation of close contacts. Those who were close to the scene and did not wear masks were also included.

"In addition to looking at the location, we also need to determine the flow of people to and from the infusion room. For example, although not sitting near Li, but some patients may get up to go to the toilet when Li side, or there is a brief stand beside its situation, this may also be close contacts. In this case, we also track which seat the patients returned to and write down the seat number."

After initial scoping of contacts within the hospital, the hospital quickly responded with contact information for these people. The Centers for Disease Control and Prevention contacted one by one to check, such as asking the other party was wearing the mask type, whether physical discomfort, etc. .

"Most People's first reaction to our phone calls is understandably nervous. So in the meantime, we also pay attention to pacify the work, but also told the other party to do a good job of home quarantine, pending further notice."

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Dispatch vehicles standing by

At 11 p.m. on Feb. 2, the CDC completed a detailed flow report.

While the CDC was busy working, the Public Security Department also acted quickly according to the CDC's Road Map of activities, eventually demarcating another eight close contacts, and the CDC conducted another round of telephone review.

Before Li's test results came out, the Jinshan District Epidemic Prevention and Control Command had obtained the list of the 55 close contacts.

This is also the largest number of close contacts among the three confirmed cases in Jinshan District.

Fortunately, these 55 close contacts, have now lifted the concentration of quarantine, safely back home.
